Sentencas: We report the fabrication and evaluation of a platinum nanowire network as a highly efficient current collector for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: A platinum nanowire network as a highly efficient current collector for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The ink of carbon-black supported platinum nanoparticles was sprayed onto the cathode.
Titulo: A platinum nanowire network as a highly efficient current collector for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: After firing, the carbon black was oxidized and disappeared as carbon dioxide gas while the platinum nanoparticles connect with one another, forming a tree-branch-like nanowire network.
Titulo: A platinum nanowire network as a highly efficient current collector for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The diameters of the nanowires range from 100 nm to 400 nm.
Titulo: A platinum nanowire network as a highly efficient current collector for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Compared to a conventional platinum paste current collector, the polarization resistance of the PrBaCo2O5+delta (PBCO) cathode with a nanowire current collector was reduced by 44% at 650 degrees C (from 0.18 Omega cm(2) to 0.1 Omega cm(2)).
Titulo: A platinum nanowire network as a highly efficient current collector for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The peak power density of the button cells was improved at different degrees of 31.8-59.6% under temperatures 650-550 degrees C for typical cathode materials of PBCO, La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF), and Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta (BSCF).
Titulo: A platinum nanowire network as a highly efficient current collector for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The nanowire network did not show obvious changes after long term testing (400 h).
Titulo: A platinum nanowire network as a highly efficient current collector for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
